import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Count the number of occurrences of each restaurant type
    restaurant_counts = data['key'].value_counts()

    # Create a bar chart of restaurant types
    chart = sns.barplot(x=restaurant_counts.index, y=restaurant_counts.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of restaurant types in the U-District dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Restaurant Types')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    chart.legend(title='Restaurant Types', loc='upper right', labels=restaurant_counts.index)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of latitude values in the U-District dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
